                        "description": "20 outbred Sprague-Dawley rats which were 8\u20139 weeks old at the beginning of the experiment were used in this study. The blood was taken after 2 weeks of experiment using procedure for tail snip blood sample collection. Blood from different animals was not taken at the same time as this was done in combination with other scheduled animal examinations. In this study, serum was used after removing all blood cells by centrifugation (3000 rpm, 15 min). After 4 weeks, in the end of pathology model experiment, rats were sacrificed by decapitation, and liver, brain and serum from each animal were collected, frozen at -80 \u00b0C and stored until sample preparation (for 1 month). </p> The alcohol-induced pathology was modeled over the period of 4 weeks. All animals were divided into 2 experimental groups (10 animals in each group):</br> 1) Control group C: Animals received intragastrically 5 ml of water twice a day (9:00 a.m. and 9:00 p.m.).</br> 2) Alcohol group A: Alcohol was gavaged by rat probe twice a day (9:00 a.m. and 9:00 p.m.). The alcohol dosage was specified above in section 2.1. The average alcohol dose was 10-12 g/kg per day.</br>",
